# Changelog

## Version 0.1.3 (2017-02-07)

- Features

    - [http Basic authentication](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basic_access_authentication) supported by [Flask-BasicAuth](https://github.com/jpvanhal/flask-basicauth)

## Version 0.1.2 (2017-02-06)

- Features

    - SMTP mail, compatible with asynchronous mode, supported by [Flask-Mail](https://github.com/mattupstate/flask-mail)

- Bugfixes

    - Fixed an issue where celery is binded with context of local flask instance not global flask instance.
    - Fixed an issue where importing variables in wsgi.py, not in application package, which changing testing environment.

- Miscellaneous

    - Refactor initialization using decorators
    - Refactor authentication using database

## Version 0.1.1 (2017-02-04)

- Features

    - Asynchronous queue supported by [Celery](https://github.com/celery/celery)

## Version 0.1.0 (2017-01-23)

- Features

    - [Bootstrap](http://getbootstrap.com/) supported by [Flask-Bootstrap](https://github.com/mbr/flask-bootstrap/)
    - Database supported by [Flask-SQLAlchemy](https://github.com/mitsuhiko/flask-sqlalchemy)
    - Task scheduling supported by [APScheduler](https://github.com/agronholm/apscheduler)
    - Authentication with database backend supported by [Flask-Login](https://github.com/maxcountryman/flask-login)
    - [Wechat Official Account](https://mp.weixin.qq.com/) supported by [WeRoBot](https://github.com/whtsky/WeRoBot)
    - [Heroku](https://heroku.com/)/[Dokku](https://github.com/dokku/dokku)/[Flynn](https://github.com/flynn/flynn) supported
